          "process_md": "&gt; **Registration Process:**\n\n**Step 1:** Visit the [**official website**](https://bcebconline.bihar.gov.in/cspy/EBCscholarship/Index.aspx). Click &amp;quot;[**New Registration**](https://bcebconline.bihar.gov.in/cspy/EBCscholarship/PETC_Terms.aspx)&amp;quot; option, in case of a new applicant. \n**Step 2:** In case of **&amp;quot;New Registration&amp;quot;** carefully read the &amp;quot;Guidelines for Registration&amp;quot; and click &amp;quot;Continue.&amp;quot;\n**Step 3:** On successful login**,** enter the form by entering your personal details, educational qualifications, and other required information.\n**Step 4:** Upload your photograph, signature, and any necessary documents.\n**Step 5:** Ensure all fields marked with an asterisk (*) are filled in correctly.\n**Step 6:** Once all the required information is entered, click the &amp;quot;Submit&amp;quot; button. Upon successful submission, you will receive a registration ID and password.\n&gt; **Process to apply for scheme:**\n\n**Step 1:** In case already registered, then click on &amp;quot;**A**[**pplicant Login**](https://bcebconline.bihar.gov.in/cspy/EBCscholarship/Login.aspx)&amp;quot; option. \n**Step 2:** Enter your User ID, Password, and the verification code.\n**Step 3:** Click &amp;quot;Login&amp;quot; to access your account and fill out the application form.\n**Step 4:** Verify your entries before submitting the application. No modifications can be made after the final submission.\n**Step 5:** After verifying your application form, click &amp;quot;Submit&amp;quot; to save your application.\n\n  - You may print the application form as a draft.\n  - An application ID will be generated after the final submission.\n  - Only the final submission will be considered.\n\n**Step 6:** Print a copy of the finally submitted application form.\n**Note:** \n\n   1. In case the applicant faces any issue while submitting the application form, one can submit a &amp;quot;[**Request Query**](https://bcebconline.bihar.gov.in/cspy/EBCscholarship/RequestQuery.aspx)&amp;quot; to the department raising the concerns.\n"
